#PCA no cross validation

x_train<- X[1:399, ]
x_test<- X[400:499, ]

y1TR<- baresoilFrac_lnd_mean_ens_wave00[1:399, ]
y1TS<- baresoilFrac_lnd_mean_ens_wave00[400:499, ]
y1TR<- as.data.frame(y1TR)
y1TS<- as.data.frame(y1TS)

#pca
pca_y1 <- prcomp(y1TR, scale. = T)
plot(pca_y1)

y1TR_pca<- pca_y1$x[, 1]
y1TS_pca<- predict(pca_y1, newdata = y1TS)[, 1]

gp_model_y1<- km(~., design = x_train, response = y1TR_pca, nugget.estim = T,
                 control = list(trace = FALSE))
predictions_y1<- predict.km(gp_model_y1, newdata = x_test, type = "UK")

plot(y1TS_pca, predictions_y1$mean, xlab = "True Values", ylab = "Predicted Values", main = "True vs Predicted Values")
abline(a = 0, b = 1, col = "red")

mae <- mean(abs(predictions_y1$mean - y1TS_pca))
range_true <- max(y1TS_pca) - min(y1TS_pca)
mae_percentage <- (mae / range_true) * 100
print(mae_percentage)

## [1] 11.26535
y7TR<- fLuc_lnd_sum_ens_wave00[1:399, ]
y7TS<- fLuc_lnd_sum_ens_wave00[400:499, ]
y7TR<- as.data.frame(y7TR)

pca_y7 <- prcomp(y7TR, scale. = T)
plot(pca_y7)

y7TR_pca<- pca_y7$x[, 1:3]
y7TS_pca<- predict(pca_y7, newdata = y7TS)[, 1:3]
y7TS<- as.data.frame(y7TS)

npcs7<- 3

predictions_list7 <- list()
mae_list7 <- list()
mae_percentage_list7 <- list()

for (i in 1:npcs7) {
  # Extract the i-th principal component for training and testing data
  y_train_pca_i <- y7TR_pca[, i]
  y_test_pca_i <- y7TS_pca[, i]
  
  # Fit Gaussian Process Regression model
  gp_model_y7 <- km(~., design = x_train, response = y_train_pca_i, nugget.estim = T, control = list(trace = FALSE))
  
  # Make predictions
  predictions_y7 <- predict.km(gp_model_y7, newdata = x_test, type = "UK")
  
  # Store predictions
  predictions_list7[[i]] <- predictions_y7$mean
  
  # Calculate Mean Absolute Error (MAE)
  mae7 <- mean(abs(predictions_y7$mean - y_test_pca_i))
  
  # Calculate the range of the true values for this PC
  range_true7 <- max(y_test_pca_i) - min(y_test_pca_i)
  
  # Calculate MAE as a percentage of the range of the true values
  mae_percentage7 <- (mae7 / range_true7) * 100
  
  # Store MAE and MAE percentage
  mae_list7[[i]] <- mae7
  mae_percentage_list7[[i]] <- mae_percentage7
}

mae_df7 <- data.frame(PC = 1:npcs7, MAE = unlist(mae_list7), MAE_percentage = unlist(mae_percentage_list7))
print(mae_df7)
##   PC      MAE MAE_percentage
## 1  1 4.945545       9.327964
## 2  2 1.725221       9.016483
## 3  3 1.753519       4.905301
par(mfrow = c(1, 3))  
for (i in 1:npcs7) {
  plot(y7TS_pca[, i], predictions_list7[[i]], xlab = "True Values", ylab = "Predicted Values", 
       main = paste("True vs Predicted Values (PC", i, ")"))
  abline(a = 0, b = 1, col = "red")
}

#K-fold cross validation for y1 and y9

modeling_function <- function(train_index, test_index) {
  x_train_cv <- x_train[train_index, ]
  y1TR_cv <- y1TR[train_index, ]
  x_test_cv <- x_train[test_index, ]
  y1TS_cv <- y1TR[test_index, ]
  
  # PCA
  pca_y1 <- prcomp(y1TR_cv, scale. = TRUE)
  y1TR_pca <- pca_y1$x[, 1]
  y1TS_pca <- predict(pca_y1, newdata = y1TS_cv)[, 1]
  
  # Gaussian Process Model
  gp_model_y1 <- km(~., design = x_train_cv, response = y1TR_pca, nugget.estim = TRUE,
                    control = list(trace = FALSE))
  predictions_y1 <- predict.km(gp_model_y1, newdata = x_test_cv, type = "UK")
  
  # Calculate MAE
  mae <- mean(abs(predictions_y1$mean - y1TS_pca))
  range_true <- max(y1TS_pca) - min(y1TS_pca)
  mae_percentage <- (mae / range_true) * 100
  
  return(list(mae_percentage = mae_percentage, 
              true_values = y1TS_pca, 
              predicted_values = predictions_y1$mean))
}
set.seed(123) 
cv_folds <- createFolds(1:399, k = 5, list = TRUE, returnTrain = TRUE)

cv_results <- lapply(cv_folds, function(train_index) {
  test_index <- setdiff(1:399, train_index)
  modeling_function(train_index, test_index)
})

mae_percentages <- sapply(cv_results, function(result) result$mae_percentage)
mean_cv_mae <- mean(mae_percentages)
print(mae_percentages)
##    Fold1    Fold2    Fold3    Fold4    Fold5 
## 15.61325 12.88216 10.00174 10.09069 11.85286
print(mean_cv_mae)
## [1] 12.08814
plot_list <- lapply(seq_along(cv_results), function(i) {
  result <- cv_results[[i]]
  ggplot(data = data.frame(True = result$true_values, Predicted = result$predicted_values),
         aes(x = True, y = Predicted)) +
    geom_point() +
    geom_abline(intercept = 0, slope = 1, color = "red") +
    labs(title = paste("Fold", i, "True vs Predicted Values"),
         x = "True Values", y = "Predicted Values") +
    theme_minimal()
})

for (plot in plot_list) {
  print(plot)
}

#k-fold y9

npcs9<- 9

modeling_function9 <- function(train_index, test_index) {
  x_train_cv <- x_train[train_index, ]
  x_test_cv <- x_train[test_index, ]
  y9TR_cv <- y9TR[train_index, ]
  y9TS_cv <- y9TR[test_index, ]
  
  # Initialize lists to store results for each PC
  mae_percentages9 <- vector("list", length = npcs9)
  true_values9 <- vector("list", length = npcs9)
  predicted_values9 <- vector("list", length = npcs9)
  
  for (i in 1:npcs9) {
    # PCA
    pca_y9 <- prcomp(y9TR_cv, scale. = TRUE)
    y_train_pca <- pca_y9$x[, i]
    y_test_pca <- predict(pca_y9, newdata = y9TS_cv)[, i]
    
    # Gaussian Process Model
    gp_model_y9 <- km(~., design = x_train_cv, response = y_train_pca, nugget.estim = TRUE,
                      control = list(trace = FALSE))
    predictions_y9 <- predict.km(gp_model_y9, newdata = x_test_cv, type = "UK")
    
    # Calculate MAE
    mae9 <- mean(abs(predictions_y9$mean - y_test_pca))
    range_true9 <- max(y_test_pca) - min(y_test_pca)
    mae_percentage9 <- (mae9 / range_true9) * 100
    
    # Store results for the i-th PC
    mae_percentages9[[i]] <- mae_percentage9
    true_values9[[i]] <- y_test_pca
    predicted_values9[[i]] <- predictions_y9$mean
  }
  
  return(list(mae_percentages9 = mae_percentages9,
              true_values9 = true_values9,
              predicted_values9 = predicted_values9))
}

cv_results9 <- lapply(cv_folds, function(train_index) {
  test_index <- setdiff(1:399, train_index)
  modeling_function9(train_index, test_index)
})

mae_percentages9 <- vector("list", length = npcs9)
for (i in 1:npcs9) {
  mae_percentages9[[i]] <- sapply(cv_results9, function(result) result$mae_percentages9[[i]])
}
mean_mae_percentages9 <- sapply(mae_percentages9, mean)

print(mae_percentages9)

plot_list9 <- lapply(seq_along(cv_results9), function(i) {
  result <- cv_results9[[i]]
  
  plot_grid <- lapply(1:npcs9, function(pc_index) {
    true_values <- unlist(result$true_values9[[pc_index]])
    predicted_values <- unlist(result$predicted_values9[[pc_index]])
    
    ggplot(data = data.frame(True = true_values, Predicted = predicted_values),
           aes(x = True, y = Predicted)) +
      geom_point() +
      geom_abline(intercept = 0, slope = 1, color = "red") +
      labs(title = paste("Fold", i, "PC", pc_index, "True vs Predicted Values"),
           x = "True Values", y = "Predicted Values") +
      theme_minimal()
  })
  
  # Return the list of plots for current fold
  return(plot_grid)
})

for (plot_grid in plot_list9) {
  gridExtra::grid.arrange(grobs = plot_grid, ncol = 3)
}
